The paper deals with error correction codes, specifically low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes, and their performance over different channels. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also proposes an algorithm for exhaustively determining bad patterns in LDPC codes, which involves searching and analyzing the code structure, making it relevant to the computer science (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance of LDPC codes in communication networks, which falls under the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
